==English==

===Etymology===
French, from vitre, pane of glass, from Old French, glass, window with multiple lights, from Latin vitrum

===Noun===

#A glass-paneled [[cabinet]] or [[case]] for displaying articles such as [[china]], objects d'art, or fine merchandise.

